def cleaning_data(noizy_comment):
    noizy_comment= re.sub(r'http\S+', '', noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = noizy_comment.lower()
    noizy_comment = re.sub(r"what's", "what is ", noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = re.sub(r"\'s", " ", noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = re.sub(r"\'ve", " have ", noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = re.sub(r"can't", "cannot ", noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = re.sub(r"n't", " not ", noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = re.sub(r"i'm", "i am ", noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = re.sub(r"\'re", " are ", noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = re.sub(r"\'d", " would ", noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = re.sub(r"\'ll", " will ", noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = re.sub(r"\'scuse", " excuse ", noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = re.sub(r'\W', ' ', noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = re.sub(' +',' ',noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = re.sub(r'\n','',noizy_comment)
    noizy_comment = noizy_comment.strip(' ')
    cleaned_comment = noizy_comment
    return cleaned_comment

def data_set_cleaning(noizy_data_set):
    cleaned_text = []
    for i in range(0,len(noizy_data_set)):
        text_cleaning = cleaning_data(noizy_data_set[i])
        cleaned_text.append(text_cleaning)
    noizy_data_set = pd.Series(cleaned_text).astype(str)
    return noizy_data_set

train_text = data_set_cleaning(train_text)
test_text = data_set_cleaning(test_text)

word_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(
    max_df=0.85,
    min_df=3,
    sublinear_tf=True,
    strip_accents='unicode',
    analyzer='word',
    token_pattern=r'\w{1,}',
    stop_words='english',
    ngram_range=(1, 1),
    max_features=10000)

word_vectorizer.fit(train_text)

train_word_features = word_vectorizer.transform(train_text)
test_word_features = word_vectorizer.transform(test_text)

    min_df=3,

classifier = LogisticRegression(class_weight="balanced",solver="lbfgs") # Попробуйте разные параметры, найтдите оттимальные на кросс-валидации

n_jobs = max(cpu_count()-1, 1)

scores= []

for class_name in class_names:
    train_target = train[class_name]

    cv_score = np.mean(cross_val_score(classifier, train_features, train_target, scoring='roc_auc',n_jobs=n_jobs))
    
    print('CV score for class {} is {}'.format(class_name, cv_score))
    scores.append(cv_score)

print('Total score is {}'.format(np.mean(scores)))

def add_clean_class(df: pd.DataFrame):
    toxicity_types = df.columns[2:]
    rowsum = df[toxicity_types].sum(axis=1)
    df['not_toxic'] = rowsum.apply(lambda x: 0 if x>0 else 1)
    toxicity_types = df.columns[2:]
    print(df['not_toxic'].sum())
    
    return df, toxicity_types

def plot_class_distribution(df: pd.DataFrame, colors: list):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(9,6))
    x = df.iloc[:,2:].sum()
    palette= sns.xkcd_palette(colors)
    ax = sns.barplot(x.index, x.values,palette=palette)
    plt.title('Class')
    plt.ylabel('Occurrences', fontsize=12)
    plt.xlabel('Type')
    
    rects = ax.patches
    labels = x.values
    for rect, label in zip(rects, labels):
        height = rect.get_height()
        ax.text(rect.get_x() + rect.get_width()/2, height + 10, label, 
            ha='center', va='bottom')
    plt.show()

def plot_words(wordcloud: dict, toxicity: list):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(4, 2, figsize=(24,24))
    
    for i in range(0,7):
        ax = axes[i//2,i%2] # if row >=2
        ax.imshow(wordcloud[toxicity[i]])
        ax.axis('off')
    plt.show()
In [20]:
def create_dictionary(df: pd.DataFrame, toxicity: list):
    toxity_dict = dict()
    for i in toxicity:
        text = df[df[i] == 1]['comment_text'].str.cat(sep=' ')
        wordcloud = WordCloud(stopwords=STOPWORDS, background_color='white', width=500, max_words=500, height=500).generate(text)
        toxity_dict[i] = wordcloud
    return toxity_dict
In [21]:
def wordcloud_create_plot(df: pd.DataFrame, toxicity: list):
    words_dicts = create_dictionary(df, toxicity)
    plot_words(words_dicts, toxicity)
    return words_dicts

def get_complexity(text):
    '''
    return:
    number of unique words,
    avg char in word
    avg words in sentence
    proportion unique words to all words
    '''
    num_chars = len(text)
    words = word_tokenize(text)
    num_words = len(words)
    num_sentences = len(sent_tokenize(text))
    vocabulary = {x.lower() for x in words}
    return len(vocabulary), int(num_chars/num_words), int(num_words/num_sentences), len(vocabulary)/num_words

def text_cleaner(comment, mode='a'):
#     '!"#$%&\'()*+,-./:;<=>?@[\\]^_`{|}~'
    if mode=='a':
        comment = re.sub(r'http\S+', ' ', comment)
        comment = re.sub(r'"',' ', comment)
        comment = re.sub(r',', ' ', comment)
        comment = re.sub(r'\n',' ',comment)
        comment = comment.strip()
        comment = re.sub(' +',' ', comment)
        return comment
    elif mode=='b':
        comment = re.sub(r'"',' ', comment)
        comment = re.sub(r',', ' ', comment)
        comment = re.sub(' +',' ', comment)
        return comment

def vectorization(df_train: pd.DataFrame, df_test: pd.DataFrame,col: str, word_vectorizer, char_vectorizer):
    word_vectorizer.fit(df_train[col])
    char_vectorizer.fit(df_train[col])
    
    word_train = word_vectorizer.transform(df_train[col])
    char_train = char_vectorizer.transform(df_train[col])
    
    word_test = word_vectorizer.transform(df_test[col])
    char_test = char_vectorizer.transform(df_test[col])
    
    stack_train = hstack([word_train, char_train])
    stack_test = hstack([word_test, char_test])
    return stack_train, stack_test
